quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,1,"Qāf<sup>1</sup>. By the Glorious Qur’an!","[1] See footnote 2:1."
  50,2,"But they wonder that a warner has come to them from among themselves, so the disbelievers say, “This is something strange!",""
  50,3,"What! Is it when we die and become dust [will we return to life]? That is a far-fetched return.”",""
  50,4,"We certainly know what the earth consumes of them [after their death], and with Us is a Preserved Record<sup>2</sup>.","[2] Or a Record that preserves everything."
  50,5,"Rather they rejected the truth when it came to them, so they are in a state of confusion<sup>3</sup>.","[3] They are in confusion concerning the Qur’an, claiming that it is poetry, magic, or ancient fables. They are also in confusion concerning the Prophet (ﷺ), claiming that he is a poet, a fabricator, or insane."
  50,6,"Have they not then looked at the sky above them – how We built it and adorned it [with stars], and it has no rifts?",""
  50,7,"And We have spread out the earth and set therein firm mountains, and caused to grow therein plants of every pleasant kind,",""
  50,8,"as a source of insight and a reminder to every slave who turns [to Allah].",""
  50,9,"And We send down from the sky blessed rain, with which We cause to grow gardens and grain for harvest,",""
  50,10,"and towering palm trees having clustered fruit,",""
  50,11,"as a provision for people, and We revive thereby a dead land; likewise will be the resurrection.",""
  50,12,"The people of Noah rejected [the truth] before them<sup>4</sup>, as well as the companions of the Well<sup>5</sup> and Thamūd,","[4] i.e., before the pagans of Makkah.\n [5] i.e., people of prophet Shu‘ayb or other people. See footnote 25:38."
  50,13,"and so did ‘Ād, Pharaoh, the people of Lot,",""
  50,14,"and the dwellers of the Forest<sup>6</sup>, and the people of Tubba‘<sup>7</sup>. All of them rejected the messengers, so My warning was fulfilled.","[6] i.e., the people of Shu‘ayb (عليه السلام).\n [7] Tubba‘ al-Himyari, an ancient righteous Yemeni king. See 44:37."
  50,15,"Were We wearied by their first creation? No indeed, yet they are in confusion concerning the second creation.",""
